item.description:
arXiv:2504.05063v1 Announce Type: new 
Abstract: A search for the doubly-charmed-baryon decay ${\it \Xi}_{cc}^{++}\to{\it \Xi}_{c}^{0}(\to p K^{-}K^{-}\pi^{+})\pi^{+}\pi^{+}$ is performed using proton-proton collision data collected by the LHCb experiment at a centre-of-mass energy of 13 $\text{TeV}$ and corresponding to an integrated luminosity of 5.4 $\text{fb}^{-1}$. A significant structure consistent with the ${\it \Xi}_{cc}^{++}$ baryon is observed in the ${\it \Xi}_{c}^{0} \pi^{+} \pi^{+}$ invariant-mass spectrum. Using the ${\it \Xi}_{cc}^{++}\to{\it \Lambda}_{c}^{+}(\to pK^{-}\pi^{+})K^{-}\pi^{+}\pi^{+}$ decay as the normalisation channel, the branching fraction ratio \begin{equation*}
  \frac{{\cal B}({\it \Xi}_{cc}^{++} \to {\it \Xi}_{c}^{0}\pi^{+}\pi^{+})\times{\cal B}({\it \Xi}_{c}^{0}\to pK^{-}K^{-}\pi^{+})} {{\cal B}({\it \Xi}_{cc}^{++}\to{\it \Lambda}_{c}^{+} K^{-}\pi^{+}\pi^{+})\times{\cal B}({\it \Lambda}_{c}^{+}\to pK^{-}\pi^{+})} \end{equation*} is measured to be $0.105\pm 0.014\text{\,(stat)} \pm 0.007\text{\,(syst)}$.
